GHANAIAN actress Juliet Ibrahim believes that being single will save her from getting in a wrong relationship. “Being single will save you a thousand times more stress than being in the wrong relationship,” she said on Instagram. The actress is still in South Africa, where she celebrated her birthday recently. In a patriotic spirit, the actress, on March 6, paid a courtesy visit to the Ghana High Commission in South Africa, where she met with Mr. George Ayisi-Boateng, Ghana’s ambassador to South Africa in celebration of Ghana’s Independence Day. The actress/singer in a picture she posted with the commissioner, wrote, “Happy Independence Day Ghana. A special visit to the Ghana High Commission in South Africa, photographed with the ambassador Mr George Ayisi-Boateng.”